<P><Q REND="inline">597.&mdash;TYRTAEUS.]</Q> An ancient Poet, who is &s;aid to have been given to the Spartans as a General by the Oracle, and to have animated the Troops by his Ver&s;es to &s;uch a degree, as to be the means of their triumph over the Me&s;&s;enians, after two defeats:
<PB N="132" REF="194">
to which Ro&s;common alludes in his <HI>E&s;&s;ay on Tran&s;lated Ver&s;e.</HI></P>
